item.title: Compiler error message, please help!
item.dc:creator: @pure2ownage Pure_
item.description:
@pure2ownage wrote:

[quote=“Shorty626, post:10, topic:342464”]Lol. K. Lets break down the compilers error message so some of you 12 year olds can understand what is going on here.

When you write a class, You have to open and close the instruction set. If you do not close it, Then the compiler thinks that the instruction set is not complete and it throws an error because there is nothing after it but new classes. He is missing a Closing bracket in his code.

Can’t simplify that anymore.

[quote author=deathschaos9 link=topic=438872.msg3225281#msg3225281 date=1275519453]

To many brackets: Class, Interface, or Enum Expected.
Not enough brackets: Reached end of file while parsing.

But you also have to take into consideration which bracket, opening or closing, is shown in the error.

Never seen that error thrown with an opening bracket. So your saying his class is closed but he has more methods after the class is closed?

Yes, something like this:

public class Foo {
    //...
}
{
//doSomething();
}

So essentially he replaced his closing bracket with an opening bracket?
[/quote][/quote]
your fucking 10 though; thats why you dont display your age on your profile.
